Creating Indexes
To create an index on a table column, you can use the CREATE INDEX statement.

CREATE INDEX index_name ON tablename (column1, column2, ...);
Replace index_name with a name for your index, tablename with the table name, and column1, column2, etc., with the columns you want to index.

Example:

CREATE INDEX username_index ON users (username);
This creates an index named username_index on the username column in the users table.

Viewing Indexes
You can view the indexes associated with a table using the SHOW INDEX statement.

SHOW INDEX FROM tablename;
Replace tablename with the name of your table.

Example:

SHOW INDEX FROM users;
This command displays information about the indexes associated with the users table.

Dropping Indexes
If needed, you can drop an index from a table using the DROP INDEX statement.

DROP INDEX index_name ON tablename;
Replace index_name with the name of the index you want to drop and tablename with the name of the table.

Example:

DROP INDEX username_index ON users;
This removes the username_index from the users table.
